Description: Neck of Rhodian pottery transport amphora; oval handles with moderate curvature; near fine buff-brown clay. Two circular stamps, worn; red stripe painted around top of neck.
Curator's comments: Commented on and drawn by Petrie, Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 95. Petrie read Philiadou or Philaidou as the reading of the eponym, and Phili seems clear; yet the only eponym whose name might fit, Philinos, is not attested as using rose stamps, and is earlier than the shape of the neck warrants.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0629)
